CBD DELI IS HUGE and more impressive than Whole Foods or Fresh Market;
ANGUS STEAK, BAJA CHICKEN & CHIPOTLE sandwiches, etc.: most less than $10;
BEST AFFORDABLE OLIVE SALAD: 32 ounces at $8; Central Grocery: $19!

I consider the CBD Rouse's to be more of a humongously oversized corner deli than a grocery chain. The old A&P location in the Quarter is my neighborhood store.  However, I'd never been to its mega food counter on Baronne until recently.  What a great experience!  It reminds me of the incredibly efficient food halls at Harrod's rather than the cramped prissiness of Whole Foods.  And besides sandwiches it also specializes in hot local New Orleans takeout at non-trendy gourmand prices.  The hours are great too: 6AM to midnight.  Negatives: limited produce section, & crummy prepackaged options (one of the worst muffs in the city).
